---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Photography — Camera Terms That Develop Points"
  description="Photography words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. EXPOSURE (17pts), FLASHY (15pts), PIXEL (14pts). Camera vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble photography words, exposure scrabble points, flashy scrabble, pixel scrabble word, camera terms scrabble, photo words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Photography — Camera Terms That Develop Points","description":"Photography words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. EXPOSURE (17pts), FLASHY (15pts), PIXEL (14pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-photography"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is EXPOSURE worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"EXPOSURE scores 17 points (E=1, X=8, P=3, O=1, S=1, U=1, R=1, E=1) as an 8-letter word. The X tile provides nearly half the scoring power at 8 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PIXEL a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PIXEL scores 14 points (P=3, I=1, X=8, E=1, L=1). It's valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. The X=8 tile makes this 5-letter word score like a much longer one."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play FLASHY in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! FLASHY scores 15 points (F=4, L=1, A=1, S=1, H=4, Y=4). It uses three 4-point tiles (F, H, Y) making it one of the highest-scoring 6-letter photography-related words."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Photography — Camera Terms That Develop Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Photography vocabulary is rich with X, F, and H tiles — premium letters that most players struggle to place. Camera terms like EXPOSURE deploy X for 8 points while FLASHY stacks three 4-point tiles in a single word. Think of these as the high-ISO settings of your Scrabble game.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">EXPOSURE (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FLASHY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PIXEL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FOCUS</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Photography Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">EXPOSURE — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">E=1, X=8, P=3, O=1, S=1, U=1, R=1, E=1 · 8 letters · Uses X tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The amount of light reaching the sensor. EXPOSURE delivers 17 points with X=8 as the anchor. At 8 letters it's a strong candidate for connecting through existing board letters, though too long for a standard bingo.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📸 FLASHY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">15 pts · F=4, L=1, A=1, S=1, H=4, Y=4 · Showy/bright</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🖥️ PIXEL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · P=3, I=1, X=8, E=1, L=1 · Image unit</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔍 FOCUS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · F=4, O=1, C=3, U=1, S=1 · Sharpness</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📷 SHUTTER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · S=1, H=4, U=1, T=1, T=1, E=1, R=1 · Light gate</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Camera Vocabulary</h2>
      <p>Photography terms that play well on the Scrabble board:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FRAME</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SHOOT</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BOKEH</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CROP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FILTER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ZOOM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">15pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Photography Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PIXEL places X elegantly:</span> At 14 points from 5 tiles, PIXEL (2.8 ppt) gives you a clean X placement while keeping two tiles in reserve. The surrounding letters are all common draws.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FLASHY stacks triple-4s:</span> F=4, H=4, Y=4 all in one word means 12 points from three tiles alone. FLASHY turns an F+H+Y rack into 15 points with just 3 common fillers.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">ZOOM uses double-O:</span> Stuck with two O tiles? ZOOM (15pts) deploys them alongside Z=10 and M=3 for a compact 4-letter power play.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Photography words are <span class="text-white font-medium">X-tile specialists</span>. EXPOSURE (X=8), PIXEL (X=8), and related terms give you multiple options whenever you draw the X tile. Combined with F+H+Y stacking in words like FLASHY, camera vocabulary covers the full range of awkward premium tiles.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid photography word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Gardening</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-astronomy/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Astronomy</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-martial-arts/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Martial Arts</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-ceramics/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Ceramics</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-pirate/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Pirates</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
